				\begin{document}$N^{i}_{X^{T}Y}$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M42"><mml:msubsup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>N</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:msup><mml:mrow><mml:mi>X</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>T</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msup><mml:mi>Y</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:msubsup></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13059_2021_2553_Article_IEq21.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> are the noise matrices, and <italic>i</italic> is the index of a client, and sends them to the server. The compensator summarizes noise from clients to global noise 
<disp-formula id="Equa"><alternatives><tex-math id="M43">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
